{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3741921,"name":"Austin Yu","username":"Justmore5mins","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/278dde/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-09-18T14:41:34.493Z","cooked":"<p>Hi <span class="abbreviation">CD<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Chief Delphi"></template></span> it’s leader programmer from <span class="abbreviation">FRC<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="FIRST Robotics Competition"></template></span> team 8569 speaking.</p>
<p>We’re programming the chassis for the FreshMan Cup(a small game co-hosted by some schools)</p>
<p>And while simulating the drivetrain (DifferentialDrive, LTV), we uses this function to generate the path on the fly</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">public Command drive(Pose2d pose) {
        try {
            return new PathfindingCommand(pose, frc.robot.Auto.Constants.AutoConstaints,
                    () -&gt; PoseEstmator.getEstimatedPosition(),
                    () -&gt; Constants.kinematics.toChassisSpeeds(getSpeeds()),
                    (speeds, ff) -&gt; setSpeed(Constants.kinematics.toWheelSpeeds(speeds)),
                    new PPLTVController(0.02, 5676 * Constants.VelocityConvertionFactor),
                    RobotConfig.fromGUISettings(),
                    this);
        } catch (Exception e) {
            return runOnce(() -&gt; DriverStation.reportError("failed at generating path", e.getStackTrace()));
        }
</code></pre>
<p>But it drives snake-like trajectory like this</p>
<p><div class="lightbox-wrapper"><a class="lightbox" href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/4X/b/f/1/bf1c3939e0601d983b9c4053cab61ed25cb9b0bd.jpeg" data-download-href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/bf1c3939e0601d983b9c4053cab61ed25cb9b0bd" title="image"><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/4X/b/f/1/bf1c3939e0601d983b9c4053cab61ed25cb9b0bd_2_690x448.jpeg" alt="image" data-base62-sha1="rgDFgdFo58HlzWY5GXaIRI9Onj7" width="690" height="448" srcset="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/4X/b/f/1/bf1c3939e0601d983b9c4053cab61ed25cb9b0bd_2_690x448.jpeg, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/4X/b/f/1/bf1c3939e0601d983b9c4053cab61ed25cb9b0bd_2_1035x672.jpeg 1.5x, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/4X/b/f/1/bf1c3939e0601d983b9c4053cab61ed25cb9b0bd_2_1380x896.jpeg 2x" data-dominant-color="27282A"><div class="meta"><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#far-image"></use></svg><span class="filename">image</span><span class="informations">1920×1247 176 KB</span><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#discourse-expand"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>
<p>I’ve tried many methods and looked for answers on ChatGPT, but nothing seems to work. Could anyone help me?</p>
<p>Thank you in advance,<br>
